 be enforced. Keeping people safe on the railway is at the heart of everything we do. Safe behaviour is therefore a requirement of working for Network Rail. You should demonstrate your personal dedication to safety on your application.\",\"aboutTheRole\":{\"essential\":[\"Ability to lead, motivate, and develop a team.\",\"Relevant successful experience in managing the development of an investment portfolio.\",\"Membership of a professional body with chartered status and/or educated to degree level.\",\"Knowledge of investment processes and procedures.\",\"Knowledge and understanding of project and contract management.\",\"Good financial and commercial awareness.\",\"CDM & risk assessment (Project Safety Management course) Competence.\"],\"desirable\":[\"Knowledge of the rail industry and Network Rail�s contractual commitments to customers.\",\"Knowledge of Network Rail�s assets and how they are managed.\",\"Knowledge of business case analysis.\",\"Relevant experience working in a railway environment\"],\"keyAccountabilities\":[\"Work very closely with Regional Asset Managers in their development of RAMPs.\",\"Agree with the Contractor Construction Managers and Network Rail Project Managers the method of delivery to be adopted for each work item and guide the staging of each item.\",\"Manage the initial dating of each work item into preparatory, core, and follow up possessions to deliver an optimum programme based on deliverability and efficiency criteria in accordance with Planning Rules.\",\"Where appropriate identify packaging opportunities into campaigns and negotiate access with customers, with NDS and the NAU.\",\"Manage the production of resource estimates and cost estimates for worksites based on agreed delivery methods.\",\"Forecast resource demand and resolve resource conflicts during the long-term planning process.\",\"Secure access requirements through working with NDS. Monitor and provide reports on the booking status of possessions and provide input into the access dispute resolution process.\",\"Maintain the Regions program up to date under change control (scope, volumes, schedule, method, resources, costs) through submission for authorization of the business plan.\",\"Establish working level relationships with Regional Asset Managers, Contractors Construction Managers, Network Rail Project Managers, NDS Business Managers, and other key stakeholders.\",\"Participate in TT-65 Plan stage gates for each work item with Network Rail Project Managers.\",\"Secure and develop business growth work items in accordance with targets and requirements set by the Planning & Controls Manager.\"]}}"